Sequence – an ordered list of instructions 

  Order is important for desired outcome to be achieved.  
  
  No instruction is missed/skipped 

 

Selection (or branching) - path through the program is determined by a condition 

   Condition returns true or false to determine which code to execute 
  
  Some code may not be executed 

 

Iteration – section of code that is repeated 

  For a fixed number of times 
  
  Until a condition is met 
  
  While a condition is true 
